İlk olarak kaggle üzerinden düz bir veri dosyası indirdim. Bu bir hotel veri seti ve içinde eksik veriler; düzeltilmesi ve değiştirilmesi gereken bölümler var şu an. 
Burda hotelproject adlı bir database açtım. Açtıktan sonra Taskstan flat file diyip  import etmem lazım. Burda hatalar vericek bi kaç tane onları düzenleyerek veri setimi yüklüyorum. Hataları düzeltiyorum. Nullara izin vermem lazım çünkü null içeren bozuk sütunlar var onları ilerde düzelticem. Aynı zamanda tinyintten inte çevirmem gereken bir ksıım var burda



CREATE TABLE Staging_HotelData (
    hotel NVARCHAR(MAX), is_canceled NVARCHAR(MAX), lead_time NVARCHAR(MAX),
    arrival_date_year NVARCHAR(MAX), arrival_date_month NVARCHAR(MAX),
    arrival_date_week_number NVARCHAR(MAX), arrival_date_day_of_month NVARCHAR(MAX),
    stays_in_weekend_nights NVARCHAR(MAX), stays_in_week_nights NVARCHAR(MAX),
    adults NVARCHAR(MAX), children NVARCHAR(MAX), babies NVARCHAR(MAX),
    meal NVARCHAR(MAX), country NVARCHAR(MAX), market_segment NVARCHAR(MAX),
    distribution_channel NVARCHAR(MAX), is_repeated_guest NVARCHAR(MAX),
    previous_cancellations NVARCHAR(MAX), previous_bookings_not_canceled NVARCHAR(MAX),
    reserved_room_type NVARCHAR(MAX), assigned_room_type NVARCHAR(MAX),
    booking_changes NVARCHAR(MAX), deposit_type NVARCHAR(MAX),
    agent NVARCHAR(MAX), company NVARCHAR(MAX), days_in_waiting_list NVARCHAR(MAX),
    customer_type NVARCHAR(MAX), adr NVARCHAR(MAX),
    required_car_parking_spaces NVARCHAR(MAX), total_of_special_requests NVARCHAR(MAX),
    reservation_status NVARCHAR(MAX), reservation_status_date NVARCHAR(MAX)
);
GO
//stagingi oluşturma


INSERT INTO Staging_HotelData
SELECT * FROM [dbo].[hotel_bookings];
//staginge copy


ALTER TABLE Staging_HotelData ADD RowID INT IDENTITY(1,1);
//id ekleme


SELECT 
    hotel,
    CAST(is_canceled AS INT) AS is_canceled,
    COALESCE(CAST(lead_time AS INT), 0) AS lead_time, -- If null, set to 0
    UPPER(arrival_date_month) AS arrival_month -- Standardize case
INTO Production_HotelData
FROM Staging_HotelData;
//production tableın oluştuğu yer




-- Checking for invalid data before finalizing
SELECT 
    'Missing Lead Time' as Error_Type, COUNT(*) as Occurrences 
    FROM Staging_HotelData WHERE lead_time IS NULL
UNION
SELECT 
    'Invalid Year', COUNT(*) 
    FROM Staging_HotelData WHERE TRY_CAST(arrival_date_year AS INT) IS NULL;
//yılları kontrol eden bi kod. sorun yok burda 0 vericek yani 


DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Production_HotelData;
GO

-- 2. The Master Transformation
SELECT 
    RowID, -- The unique ID you added to Staging
    hotel,
    
    -- Cleaning Agent: Text 'NULL' becomes 0
    CASE 
        WHEN agent IS NULL OR agent = 'NULL' OR agent = '' THEN 0 
        ELSE TRY_CAST(agent AS INT) 
    END AS agent_id,
    
    -- Cleaning Children: Missing values become 0
    COALESCE(TRY_CAST(children AS INT), 0) AS children_count,
    
    -- Standardizing Types (Transform)
    CAST(is_canceled AS INT) AS is_canceled,
    COALESCE(TRY_CAST(lead_time AS INT), 0) AS lead_time,
    UPPER(arrival_date_month) AS arrival_month,
    TRY_CAST(adr AS DECIMAL(10,2)) AS daily_rate,
    
    -- Keeping original date parts for the report
    arrival_date_year,
    arrival_date_day_of_month
    
INTO Production_HotelData
FROM Staging_HotelData;
//nulları 0 yaptık. agentta null olduğunu biliyordum o yüzden onu seçtim. children kısmında da az sayıda null vardı o yüzden onları da ekledim


SELECT COUNT(*) AS Null_Agent_Count 
FROM Staging_HotelData 
WHERE agent IS NULL OR agent = 'NULL';
//bu komut ile ilk dosyadaki yakalanan null sayısını görebiliyoruz 


SELECT COUNT(*) AS Null_Agent_Count_After 
FROM Production_HotelData 
WHERE agent_id IS NULL;
//bu da kalan nulları gösteriyo production data üzerinden ve 0



-- REPORT: Comparison of NULLs before and after cleaning
SELECT 'Staging (Dirty)' AS Table_Type, COUNT(*) AS Null_Agents 
FROM Staging_HotelData WHERE agent IS NULL OR agent = 'NULL'
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Production (Clean)', COUNT(*) 
FROM Production_HotelData WHERE agent_id = 0; -- Since we converted NULL to 0
//burda da yine bir rapor kodu. verileri çektiğimiz null sayısı ile yeni dosyadaki 0 sayısını karşılaştırıyo. eşit değerler aldıklarını görerek sorunun düzeldiğini görebiliyoruz çünkü nulların hepsi 0a çevrilmiş demek bu ki amacımız buydu 




DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Production_HotelData;

SELECT 
    RowID, -- Keep the ID so we can match them perfectly
    hotel,
    CASE 
        WHEN agent IS NULL OR agent = 'NULL' THEN 0 
        ELSE TRY_CAST(agent AS INT) 
    END AS agent_id
INTO Production_HotelData
FROM Staging_HotelData;

SELECT TOP 10 
    S.RowID,
    S.agent AS Raw_Value, 
    P.agent_id AS Cleaned_Value
FROM Staging_HotelData S
JOIN Production_HotelData P ON S.RowID = P.RowID
WHERE S.agent IS NULL OR S.agent = 'NULL';
//stage tableına id eklemiştik. burda o idyi kullanarak karşılaştırma yapıyoruz. iyi anlaşılması adına aynı zamanda agent ismini agent_id olarak değiştirdik
//1. DROP TABLE IF EXISTS (The Environment Reset)
In ETL development, you rarely get the cleaning logic perfect on the first try.

What it does: It clears the previous version of your "Production" table from the database memory.

Why run it now? Since SELECT ... INTO creates a brand-new table, the script would crash if the table already existed. This command allows you to re-run your transformation every time you add a new fix (like adding the RowID or fixing the agent column) without errors.

2. The SELECT ... INTO (The Transformation Logic)
This is the heart of your Transform (T) process.

RowID: You are adding a "Surrogate Key." Since the original Kaggle data has no unique ID for each booking, you created one so you can track exactly what happens to every single row.

CASE WHEN ...: This handles the Data Inconsistency error. You are telling SQL: "If you see the word 'NULL' or an actual empty space, treat it as 0. Otherwise, treat it as a number."

TRY_CAST: This is your Data Type Enforcement. It ensures that the agent_id column in your final table is a pure Integer, which is much faster for the database to process than text.

3. The JOIN (The Integrity Validation)
This is the most important part for your "Data Quality Report" requirement.

Why run this if we already fixed it? Because in data engineering, you never assume the code worked; you prove it.

What it proves: By joining the Staging (Dirty) and Production (Clean) tables using the RowID, you are providing a side-by-side comparison.

The Result: It proves that the cleaning was accurate (the NULLs actually became 0s) and stable (no data was shifted or assigned to the wrong hotel booking).

