In a professional data pipeline, you never want to change your source data. Here is why your staging tables still have nulls and why that’s actually a good thing for your project:

1. The "Immutability" Principle
In ETL (Extract, Transform, Load), the Extract and Staging phases are meant to be a "mirror" of the raw file.

dbo.hotel_bookings & Staging_HotelData: These are your "Before" snapshots. If you changed the data here, you would lose the ability to go back and check what the original file actually looked like.

Production_HotelData: This is your "After" snapshot. This table contains the results of your hard work.
